@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1 class="mb-4">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<div style="font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 1.15rem; color: #333;">
    <p>
        Engineering is not merely about numbers and designs—it's an art grounded in steadfast principles and ethical guidelines that shape our innovations. Esteemed organizations such as the <strong>IEEE</strong> (Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers) lead the way with their rigorous <em>Code of Ethics</em>, ensuring that our technological endeavors remain honest, sustainable, and respectful of societal needs.
    </p>
    <p>
        Complementing IEEE's standards, bodies like the <strong>ACM</strong> (Association for Computing Machinery), <strong>ASME</strong> (American Society of Mechanical Engineers), and international benchmarks such as <strong>ISO</strong> (International Organization for Standardization) and <strong>NIST</strong> (National Institute of Standards and Technology) further define the rules that govern our work. Together, these guidelines form a mosaic of responsibility, ensuring that every circuit, structure, and system is designed with precision, care, and a deep commitment to the public good.
    </p>
    <p>
        At its core, the discipline of engineering is a promise: to create, innovate, and improve lives while holding steadfast to a code of integrity. In our journey to push boundaries, these timeless principles not only protect privacy and security but also inspire us to achieve excellence in every project.
    </p>
</div>

